					<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This Privacy Policy is made by Work Companion LLP (collectively, &ldquo;Work Companion&rdquo;, &ldquo;WoCo&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) and is effective as of 4th April 2019. &nbsp;This Privacy Policy is meant to help you understand what information is collected by WoCo, why we collect it and how can you update, manage, export and delete your information.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This Privacy Policy applies to all Work Companion websites that link to it, products and services provided by Work Companion through these websites, web applications, mobile applications, plugins and browser extensions. This Privacy Policy will not apply to any of our websites, products or services that have a separate privacy policy. </span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Please note that the Privacy Policy may need to be updated from time to time in order to address new issues and reflect changes on to the Work Companion Website, Mobile Application(s), Web Application(s) and other products or services.</span></p>
<p><br /><br /></p>

<h3><b>Our Commitment to Your Privacy</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Work Companion takes customer and user privacy very seriously and asks for only the information &nbsp;that is necessary and is essential for doing business, or for the specific transaction, process or step at hand. We let our customers know what information of theirs we store and have controls in place to allow them to opt out of specific engagements. Work Companion does not share Customer&rsquo;s personal information that personally identifies the Customer with advertiser&rsquo;s, such as Customer name or email, unless the Customer asks us to. &nbsp;Work Companion will not share, distribute, review or refer any Customer data i.e. host data and information. The customer data is used or reviewed only in case it is required for any support issue, resolving any problem or if required by Law as per mentioned in terms of services. Customers are expected to bear the responsibility of keeping the user id and password secure and confidential.</span></p>
<p><br /></p>

<h3><b>Collection of Information by Work Companion</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Work Companion collects information about the customer only if it is required for a legitimate purpose. Work Companion will only have information about you if (a) It has been provided by the Customer themselves, (b) Work Companion has automatically collected the information, or (c) Work Companion has obtained the information through &nbsp;a third party. </span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Here is a detailed list of various ways we use for information collection </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">:</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Account Sign-up/Registration</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> : Work Companion collects information from their Customers when they register at Work Companion or WoCo. The sign-up is required at the time of creating a WoCo account, using any of our services or promotion. Work Companion collects general information including your name, Email address and password of your WoCo account.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Event registrations and other form submissions</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> : &nbsp;Work Companion &nbsp;records information that you submit when you (a) register for any event, including webinars or seminars, (b) subscribe to our newsletter or any other mailing list, (c) submit a form in order to download any product, whitepaper, or other materials, (d) participate in contests or respond to surveys, or (e) submit a form to request customer support or to contact Work Companion for any other purpose.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Referrals :</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> If someone has referred any of our products or services to you through any of our referral programs, that person may have provided us your name, email address and other personal information. You may contact us at </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">ds@woco.co.in </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">to request that we remove your information from our database. If you provide us information about another person, or if another person gives us your information, we will only use that information for the specific reason for which it was provided to us.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Payment Processing </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: When the customer opts to use any of our services that requires a payment to be made from the customer, we ask to provide the customer name, contact information, and credit/debit card information or other payment account information. When the customer submits their card information, we store the name and address of the cardholder, the expiry date and the last four digits of the credit/debit card number. Work Companion &nbsp;does not store the actual credit/debit card information. For quick processing of future payments, if the customer has given us their approval, we may store the credit/debit card information or other payment information in an encrypted format in the secure servers of our Payment Gateway Service Providers. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Information from browsers, devices and servers</strong> <span style="font-weight: 400;">: When you visit our websites, web- applications &nbsp;Work Companion collects information that web browsers, mobile devices and servers make available, such as the internet protocol address, browser type, language preference, time zone, referring URL, date and time of access, operating system, mobile device manufacturers and mobile network information. We include these in our log files to understand more about visitors to our websites and our application users. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Information from first party cookies and tracking technologies </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: We use temporary and permanent cookies to identify users of our services and to enhance the user experience. We embed unique identifiers in our downloadable products and services to track usage of the products. We also use cookies, beacons, tags, scripts, and other similar technologies to identify visitors, track website navigation, gather demographic information about visitors and users, understand email campaign effectiveness and for targeted visitor and user engagement by tracking your activities on our websites. We only use first-party cookies and do not use third-party cookies or other third-party tracking technologies on our websites. We also use first-party Local Storage Objects (LSOs) such as HTML5 to store content information and preferences to provide certain features.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Information from application logs and mobile analytics :</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> We collect information about your use of our products, services and mobile applications from application logs and in-house usage analytics tools, and use it to understand how your business use and needs can improve our products. This information includes clicks, scrolls, features accessed, access time and frequency, errors generated, performance data, storage utilized, user settings and configurations, and devices used to access and their locations.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Information from social media sites and other publicly available sources:</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> When you interact or engage with Work Companion on social media channels such as Facebook, Twitter, Linkedin and Instagram through posts, comments, questions and other interactions, we may collect such publicly available information, including profile information, to allow us to connect with you, improve our products, or better understand user reactions and issues. Please note that once collected, this information may be retained with us even if you delete it from the referred social media channels.Work Companion may also add and update information about you, from other publicly available sources.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><br /><br /></p>


<h3><b>Purposes for using your Information</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We at Work Companion process the information for multiple purposes in order to provide the best of our services and results to our Customers/users. This information is processed for: </span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Aggregation of patterns, trends and statistics of the customers/users.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Audit, research and analysis for protection, maintenance and improvement of our products and services. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Use of data for marketing. However, at any point, the data will Not be shared with any third party without the express consent of the user from time to time. </span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Personalisation of offers, products and services offered by Work Companion to our registered customers/users from time to time and to keep our customers posted for new products and services, upcoming events, offers, promotions and other information that might be of interest to the customer/user.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Improvement in overall services and products by conducting market research to analyse market trends, customer/user demographics etc to perform data analysis. </span></li>
